editorialReviews: Editorial Reviews About the Author Ryan North is the Toronto-based creator of Dinosaur Comics, co-editor of Machine of Death, and writer of ADVENTURE TIME. He is also the creator of Project Wonderful, an auction-based ad serving system. Boston-based Shelli Paroline and Braden Lamb are the artist team behind the top-selling all-ages comic book, ADVENTURE TIME for BOOM! Studios, as well as TRICKY JOURNEYS #3 for Lerner Publishing Group. Shelli is also a founding member of the Boston Comics Roundtable.

body.description: The all-ages smash hit of the year is back with more algebraic adventures in the Land of Ooo!The all-ages hit of the year is back with a new volume collecting even more algebraic adventures! What happens when Finn the human and Jake the dog get a hold of Princess Bubblegum’s time machine and travel to go to the future? Find out in this second volume! Read more

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just like the show
reviews.reviewText: My 11 son loves the show and tore through this book in one sitting. He loves all the posters in the back too. If you or your kid loves Adventure Time, you will not be disappointed

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 11, 2013
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Even better than the first!
reviews.reviewText: I worte a glowing review for AdventureTime vol. 1, but this is even better! The story is great, and I think it takes advantage of being a comic rather than a cartoon by showing us things that would have been far too complicated to animate (Fractal Jake!). Also Ryan North's little comments and jokes written at the bottoms of the pages are always a personal joy.Mostly I loved Queen Bubblegum and all her BA costumes. So cool.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 20, 2013
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Adventure Time Comic Books
reviews.reviewText: My 10yo son and 8yo daughter love this book. They read it themselves, and out loud to their 6yo brother & 3yo sister. These are fun reading books. My wife isn't fond of the whole Adv. Time. but they are very excited and play with the toys and read the books all the time. Their mind is energized as they play make believe and use the stuffed characters to make all sorts of scenarios for hours on end.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 28, 2013
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Time for a big smile
reviews.reviewText: This is a very faithful representation of the wonderful cartoon series. Not big yucks, but you won't stop smiling, and that, to me, is worth every penny.

reviews.reviewTitle: A fun read. I'd read some of the comics from ...
reviews.reviewText: A fun read. I'd read some of the comics from other authors and they didn't quite cut it for me. But this one was a delight (there's no better word), and I'll be getting more of North's work in this series.

Reading these comics is a true joy, both for the eyes and for the soul.Friendship, monsters, time travels, video games, evil robots and good ones too.The variant cover gallery at the end is pure magic.In some sort of way it's a life changing experience, and lot of fun too!For all ages

Tot molt correcte, tant en tramitació com en rapidesa d'enviament i gestió. Crec que a l'haver comprat aquest còmic juntament amb un altre, les despeses de manipulació i enviament haurien d'haver estat la meitat. Pel demés cap problema. Recomanable.
